 // Display-Events API HTTP test requests
 // Reference: These tests for events were generated by ChatGPT and checked for validity against /backend/database/sample_data.sql
 // The transcript I used was: "Generate http test requests for this endpoint http://localhost:8080/api/events retrieving event data with the optional sort and filtering input:
//                               sortBy, radius, lat, lng, minParticipants, dateFilter, startDate, endDate"

### GET All Events
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events
Accept: application/json


### GET Upcoming Events (All future)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?dateFilter=upcoming
Accept: application/json


### GET Events This Week (next 7 days)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?dateFilter=week
Accept: application/json


### GET Events This Month (next 30 days)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?dateFilter=month
Accept: application/json


### GET Custom Date Range (Oct 25 – Oct 30 2025)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?startDate=2025-10-25&endDate=2025-10-30
Accept: application/json


### GET Within 100 mi of New York City
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?lat=40.7128&lng=-74.0060&radius=100
Accept: application/json


### GET  Within 100 mi of NYC AND Next Month
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?lat=40.7128&lng=-74.0060&radius=100&dateFilter=month
Accept: application/json


### GET Sort by Participants (descending)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?sortBy=participants
Accept: application/json


### GET Sort by Date (soonest first)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?sortBy=date
Accept: application/json


### GET Minimum Participants ≥ 4
GET http://localhost:8080/api/events?minParticipants=4
Accept: application/json




